      {
        "id": 2493127,
        "name": "Fred C",
        "username": "Fred_C",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/f/b77776/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2018-09-30T17:09:43.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=116842&amp;iNote=7261962\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2002 Yves Boyer-Martenot Meursault Les Tillets</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Meursault (9/30/2018)</em><br>\nShockingly good. Color is still light yellow. There is a touch of honey and lemon on the nose and plenty of acidic lift on the palate. Nice meursault minerality and also surprisingly no detectable oak. The finish is sneaky long. A wonderfully balanced meursault with age for $50. Hard to beat.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Photo added below for proof it was not oxidized.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=1799247&amp;iNote=7257395\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2012 Domaine Roulot Meursault 1er Cru Les Perri\u00e8res</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Meursault 1er Cru (9/27/2018)</em><br>\nThe Roulot signature and precision is undeniable. Just a touch of ripeness and oak at this stage but but people were calling the 08 too ripe a few years ago. I expect this to be as good as the 08 in 4-5 years.  I\u2019m learning Roulot MP and other great white Burgundy need 10 years to start showing their stuff. Hoard and hold for now.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em><br>\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"/uploads/db3686/original/3X/4/d/4d7cc1d890be6014297301f2febe43643cace70e.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/4d7cc1d890be6014297301f2febe43643cace70e\" title=\"B6A1DA14-5E1D-46B6-B706-41E49291E152.jpeg\"><img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/4/d/4d7cc1d890be6014297301f2febe43643cace70e_2_375x500.jpeg\" alt=\"B6A1DA14-5E1D-46B6-B706-41E49291E152.jpeg\" data-base62-sha1=\"b3u3utF7meT1HsXTHPB0obc8fE2\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/4/d/4d7cc1d890be6014297301f2febe43643cace70e_2_375x500.jpeg, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/4/d/4d7cc1d890be6014297301f2febe43643cace70e_2_562x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/4/d/4d7cc1d890be6014297301f2febe43643cace70e_2_750x1000.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"796651\"><div class=\"meta\">\n<svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">B6A1DA14-5E1D-46B6-B706-41E49291E152.jpeg</span><span class=\"informations\">1536\u00d72048 748 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg>\n</div></a></div></p>",
